Chocolate Lava Toast

If you love chocolate, you will fall in love with it all over again, I promise. This is the perfect breakfast option for Valentineâs week or to make someone feel extra special. Letâs make this.

Serves 1
3-4 bread slices
2 tbsp custard powder 
1/2 cup milk
1 tbsp sugar/jaggery/honey/maple syrup
1/2 cup milk
1 tbsp cocoa powder 
2 tbsp butter
Mix together custard powder, milk & the sweetener of your choice. Dunk the bread slices in the mixture & cook on a hot pan with butter for 2-3 minutes on each side or till golden brown. Stack the bread slices on top of each other & cut a small square from the top bread slice only. 
Now, add the leftover custard mixture to the pan with milk mixed with cocoa powder & cook for 2-3 minutes till the mixture thickens. You can add a tsp of sweetener to this mixture too. Pour the chocolate milk mixture in the cut out square. Sprinkle with cocoa powder. Serve hot & dig in.!

Substitutes
Milk - oat/almond/soy/cashew milk
Sugar - jaggery/honey/maple syrup/ date syrup 
Butter - coconut oil

Limited Edition Chickenð: Ingredients & Recipe Below:-
- Marinate 1 kg chicken with 1 tbsp each of salt, red chilli powder, 1/2 tsp turmeric and 2 tbsp ginger-garlic paste. Let it sit covered for 10-15 minutes.
- Heat 6 tbsp oil in a Kadhai and add in 2-3 strings of curry leaves. Let them pop for ten seconds. Now add in 6 thinly sliced onions. Fry on high until golden brown. Now add in the marinated chicken and fry on high for 3-4 minutes. Next close the lid turning flame to low for 10 minutes.
- Dry roast 1 tsp each of fennel seeds, cumin seeds, black peppercorns, 1 tbsp coriander seeds, 2 green cardamom, 2 cloves and 5-6 less spicy dry red chillies (remove seeds if using spicy ones) on low flame for 2.5 minutes then blend all of it together into a fine powder.
- Add this powder in the Kadhai along with 3/4th tbsp soya sauce, 1 tbsp each of tomato sauce, roasted crushed kasoori methi and 3-4 chopped green chillies. Mix well for 2 minutes on low and again close the lid on low flame for 12-15 minutes (depending on the size of your pieces) checking and stirring in between. Garnish with chopped coriander leaves and crispy fried brown onions.

Kaan Faadu Mutton: Ingredients & Recipe Below:-
- Heat 7 tbsp oil in a Kadhai and add in 8-10 garlic cloves and 4 dry red chillies. Fry on high for 15 seconds then add in 1 bay leaf, 2 green cardamom, 2 inch cinnamon, 1 mace, 5 cloves, 2 black cardamom and 1/4th nutmeg. Fry for another 20 seconds then add in 5 thinly sliced onions.
- Fry the onions on high for 5 minutes then add in 1 kg mutton and fry on high for 3 minutes. Next add in 1 tbsp salt and fry on high for another 3 minutes. Prepare a paste by blending together 2-3 onions, 10-12 cloves of garlic, 2 inch ginger, 1 string of curry leaves and half tsp carom seeds.
- Add this paste in the Kadhai and fry on high for 4 minutes. Now add in 1 tbsp each of red chilli powder, coriander powder, garam masala powder, 3/4th tbsp each of black pepper powder, roasted cumin powder and half tbsp turmeric. Then fry from high to medium for 6 minutes.
- Next add in 3 cups of warm water mixing well. Close the lid turning flame to low for 45 minutes checking and stirring in between. Now add in some chopped coriander leaves mixing well and close the lid once again for 15 minutes on low. Turn off the flame and place a flaming coal topped up with bit of chopped garlic and a clove. Add some ghee on top and close the lid for that smoky flavour in the mutton. Let it remain closed for 4 minutes then garnish with chopped coriander leaves.
